People ex rel. Barnstoff v. McLean et al., Police Commissioners. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. June 6, 1890.) Certiorari by George Barnstoff to review the action of the police commissioners in dismissing him from the police force of New York city.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

L. J. Grant, for relator. J. J. Delaney, for respondents. Van Brunt, P. J.

The proceedings in this case should be affirmed, and the writ dismissed, with costs. No opinion is written, because of the character of the points submitted upon the part of the relator. All concur.
